This whole section can be simplified, the location string is assumed to be of the format: CPU0_DIMM_A or CPU0 DIMM_A 
Something like this:

cpuPos = deviceLocator.find(substrCpu);
if (cpuPos != std::string::npos)
std::string socketString =
        deviceLocator.substr( cpuPos + substrCpu.length(), 1);
dimmPos = deviceLocator.find(substrDimm)
if (dimmPos != std::string::npos)
std::string slotString =
        deviceLocator.substr( dimmPos + substrDimm.length() + 1);



Another idea is to use regex to do the matching and str to number conversion
